      <h2>Who Is This Bird?</h2>
      <p>
        The bird in question is the <strong
          >Malabar Pied Hornbill (Anthracoceros coronatus)</strong
        >, a striking and rare species found in the forests of Sri Lanka and
        parts of the Indian subcontinent. With its oversized yellow-and-black
        casque sitting proudly atop its bill, this hornbill is not only visually
        captivating but also behaviorally fascinating.
      </p>
