      <h2>Ecological Importance</h2>
      <p>
        Malabar Pied Hornbills play a vital role in their ecosystems. By feeding
        on fruits and dispersing seeds over wide areas, they act as key seed
        dispersers, helping regenerate forests. Some tree species are almost
        entirely dependent on hornbills for reproduction.
      </p>
