      <h2>Conservation Concerns</h2>
      <p>
        Unfortunately, these birds are under pressure due to habitat
        destruction, logging, and hunting. Since they depend on large, mature
        trees for nesting, deforestation poses a serious threat to their
        survival.
      </p>
      <p>
        The pictures shown here were captured in Yala National Park, one of Sri
        Lanka's most important wildlife reserves. It is only because of
        protected national forests like Yala that species such as the Malabar
        Pied Hornbill still survive today. Without these sanctuaries, they would
        likely have been long gone. Protecting these habitats is not just about
        preserving beauty—it's about safeguarding the very existence of these
        magnificent birds.
      </p>
